The paper deals with compressed sensing and the use of a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) to solve linear inverse problems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, is a likely sub-category. Additionally, since the GAN is used to model images, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for deploying the GAN-based prior, which involves learning a network-based projector, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of measurement matrices, which is related to numerical analysis, and hence cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a convergence guarantee for the algorithm, which falls under the category of theoretical computer science, and hence cs.SI (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category.
